			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: %Dodge mod?<a name="36390"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 25 04 5:00 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Theoretically the hard caps for skills is 255. Soft caps would be skills that no longer increase but are not at the hard cap (such as bard dodge at 170 or ranger piercing at 240). These would benefit from modifiers. I believe, though, only the highest modifier will take precedence (a 3% modifier and a 5% modifier will only provide a 5% bonus to your skill).
<br />

<br />
I should note this merely supposition on my part. I've never had the time nor the inclination, really, to test. Skill modifiers tend to be small, and in my opinion anything less than a 5% increase is going to be so infinitesimal as to not do much at all.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
